lil-bro
=======

lil-bro is a research fork of maderix/ANE (https://github.com/maderix/ANE),
used under the MIT License (see LICENSE; Copyright (c) 2026 maderix).

The upstream project demonstrates that *training* is possible on the Apple
Neural Engine via reverse-engineered private APIs (a proof of concept, by the
author's own description). lil-bro builds on that foundation and adds:

  - parametric model configs (tiny -> TinyStories scale)
  - a held-out validation/eval harness (data00 train / data01 val)
  - the Muon optimizer and Multi-Token Prediction (MTP) as opt-in ablations
  - an MLX twin used as a correctness oracle (gradient diff) and GPU energy baseline
  - a tokens-to-target ablation study of DeepSeek-V4 architectural ideas at
    small dense scale

All original upstream code remains under the MIT License. Modifications and
additions in this fork are likewise MIT-licensed.
